stern world, and all were influenced both directly and indirectly by Emerson and his philosophy. Ultimately, this study demonstrates how Emerson's philosophy would become a major force of liberal reformation in American society, a force whose impact is still felt today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, Americany19th centuryvBiography. 0aLiterature and myth. 0aSocial reformerszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aTranscendentalists (New England)vBiography. 4aLiterature : American Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791480182423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791480182/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles